            </div>
            <div class="container col-md-7 safety-panel"    id="sfty-acc3">
                   <p> Our lab is equipped with 4 biosafety cabinets, which prevent the samples we work with from 
being contaminated by either ourselves or external agents, and from contaminating our surroundings and any individual in the laboratory. As part of our protocols, we disinfected the cabinet with 70% ethanol and turned the UV light for 15 minutes minimum before using the biosafety cabinets. When introducing our hands or any other material we sprayed them thoroughly with 70% ethanol. Finally, when done using the biosafety cabinets, we made sure to clean them and let the UV light sterilize them for another 15 minutes.


                    </p>
